author: taylor
msg: Optional Generic Deployment feature
Using this method, deployment of a Portlet Application can be down at servlet init() time
This requires infusing the Jetspeed servlet into a Portlet application with a separate command line tool: see the deploy-tool component.
Then the portlet application can be deployed to any application server, and when the servlet is initialized,
it attempts to register with Jetspeed 'on the fly'
This current implementation does not yet support re-deployment properly.
Im working on that next ...

author: ate
msg: Getting rid of maven warning:
Tag library requested that is not present: 'reactor' in plugin: 'null'
which was the result of the xmlns:reactor="reactor" usages in almost all maven.xml files.
This is not available anymore since at least maven 1.0 RC2
